description:
&lt;p&gt;Here at Portsmouth Hospitals University NHS Trust we have an exciting opportunity for an ambitious, dynamic and experienced leader and midwifery practitioner who has a keen interest in shaping the future of our Maternity Services here in Portsmouth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The service is looking for an experienced Midwife to join the Senior Midwifery Management Team. Reporting to the Director of Midwifery and working alongside an incredible team of maternity, divisional and trust leaders.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will support the Director of Midwifery in providing managerial leadership to all staff within Maternity Services and play a key part in developing and shaping maternity services across Portsmouth in line with the ambitions of the Better Births Agenda.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A key focus of this role will also be to manage, lead and coordinate the annual projects related to the safety action points defined by NHS Resolution Maternity Incentive Scheme. (CNST)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must have substantial experience working in a senior managerial post within Maternity Services and have extensive knowledge of the National Maternity Agenda.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be considered an excellent communicator and be an effective advisor/teacher and leader. This role is aiming to make a real difference to the quality of care delivered to women and their families across the whole of the maternity care pathway, with a specific focus on the normal childbirth agenda.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To support you in this challenging role, the Divisional team will provide an excellent support structure and will encourage your personal development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder should be educated to a minimum of Masters level or equivalent demonstrable experience and ideally will hold a post registration leadership qualification. Project management experience is also desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information or to arrange a visit please contact either: Clare Meachin, Divisional Nurse Director on 07595243465 or 02392 286000 ext. 6798 clare.meachin@porthosp.nhs.uk  or Elizabeth Rix, Chief Nurse on 02392 286000 ext. 6801 elizabeth.rix@porthosp.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Monday 16th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date: &lt;/strong&gt;Monday 30th November 2020 (Stakeholder panel in the morning)&lt;/p&gt;
